{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843581915,"sessionID":"ses_2877b9e1effesWMei9GCvRu7ve","part":{"id":"prt_d78847f8c001aeLAuMTearFYOq","messageID":"msg_d78846df5001LkvTcVzD04E3u9","sessionID":"ses_2877b9e1effesWMei9GCvRu7ve","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_09f84bac13a348a48cf71234","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore picod and JWT context","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z to understand:\n\n1. What is the `pkg/picod` module? Read all Go files in pkg/picod/ and any subdirectories\n2. Is there any existing JWT-related code anywhere in the project? Search for \"jwt\", \"JWT\", \"token\", \"auth\" patterns\n3. What is the overall project structure? Look at the top-level directory and key directories\n4. Are there any existing middleware patterns in the project?\n5. Check if there's already a proposal.md or any existing proposals in the project\n6. Look at any existing AR (Architecture Request) files or similar documentation\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- The pkg/picod module structure and purpose\n- Any existing auth/JWT patterns\n- Project structure overview\n- Existing middleware patterns\n- Any relevant configuration files (go.mod, etc.)","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2877b6803ffeZfumTEVuGLIKBs (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Here is my detailed summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis\n\n### 1. The `pkg/picod` Module -- Structure and Purpose\n\n**Purpose:** PicoD is a lightweight in-sandbox daemon that runs inside each sandbox Pod. It receives JWT-authenticated HTTP requests, executes commands within a configurable workspace jail, manages files, and provides a health check endpoint. It is the core component for AgentCube's code execution capability.\n\n**Directory Structure:**\n```\npkg/picod/\n|-- auth.go              -- AuthManager: JWT RS256 verification middleware, RSA public key loading from env\n|-- auth_test.go         -- Auth middleware tests (valid token, expired, missing header, non-RSA, body size)\n|-- config.go            -- Config struct (Port, Workspace) + ParseFlags()\n|-- config_test.go       -- Config parsing tests\n|-- execute.go           -- ExecuteHandler: command execution with timeout, working dir, env vars\n|-- execute_test.go      -- Execute handler tests (valid, timeout, empty command, working dir, env)\n|-- files.go             -- Legacy file handlers (Upload, List, Download) + sanitizePath()\n|-- files/               -- NEW structured file management subpackage (AR-016)\n|   |-- manager.go       -- FileManager interface + implementation constructor\n|   |-- types.go         -- Request/Response structs for all file ops, error definitions\n|   |-- sanitize.go      -- Path sanitization (workspace jail enforcement)\n|   |-- read.go          -- ReadFileHandler (with offset/limit)\n|   |-- write.go         -- WriteFileHandler (with offset, create_parent)\n|   |-- stat.go          -- StatFileHandler\n|   |-- list.go          -- ListFilesHandler\n|   |-- upload.go        -- UploadFileHandler (with chunked upload support)\n|   |-- download.go      -- DownloadFileHandler (with HTTP Range support)\n|   |-- delete.go        -- DeleteFileHandler (single + batch)\n|   |-- move.go          -- MoveFileHandler\n|   |-- mkdir.go         -- MkDirHandler\n|   |-- search.go        -- SearchFilesHandler\n|   |-- chmod.go         -- ChmodHandler\n|   |-- *_test.go        -- Corresponding test files\n|-- health_test.go       -- Health check tests (no auth required)\n|-- server.go            -- Server struct, route registration, Run()\n|-- server_test.go       -- Server initialization and route tests\n|-- types.go             -- Data types: ExecuteRequest/Response, FileInfo, UploadFileRequest, etc.\n|-- sanitize_test.go     -- Path sanitization tests (traversal, symlinks, absolute paths)\n```\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/auth.go` (111 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/server.go` (88 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/types.go` (51 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/config.go` (20 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/execute.go` (108 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files.go` (339 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/types.go` (204 lines)\n\n**Entry Point:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/picod/main.go`\n\n---\n\n### 2. Existing JWT/Auth Patterns\n\n**YES -- There is extensive JWT-related code in two places:**\n\n#### A. PicoD AuthManager (`pkg/picod/auth.go`)\n- **Struct:** `AuthManager` with `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey` and `sync.RWMutex`\n- **Key Loading:** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` -- reads RSA public key from `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable (PEM format)\n- **Middleware:** `AuthMiddleware() gin.HandlerFunc`:\n  - Expects `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n  - Validates RS256 signature using the loaded public key\n  - Requires `exp` and `iat` claims\n  - 1-minute clock leeway (`jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)`)\n  - Rejects non-RSA signing methods\n  - Wraps request body with `http.MaxBytesReader` (32 MiB limit) after successful auth\n  - Returns standardized 401 JSON errors\n\n#### B. Router JWTManager (`pkg/router/jwt.go`)\n- **Struct:** `JWTManager` with both `privateKey` and `publicKey`\n- **Capabilities:**\n  - `GenerateToken(claims)` -- outbound RS256 signing (Router signs tokens for PicoD)\n  - `ParseAndValidateToken(tokenString)` -- inbound token verification\n  - `PublicKey()` -- exposes the RSA public key\n  - `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` -- K8s Secret persistence (`picod-router-identity`)\n- **Key Management:** RSA 2048-bit keys, stored in K8s Secret `picod-router-identity` in namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var. Falls back to ephemeral keys outside cluster.\n- **Token Config:** 5-minute expiration, configurable issuer, 1-minute leeway\n\n#### C. Router AuthMiddleware (`pkg/router/middleware.go`)\n- Similar pattern to PicoD but uses `JWTManager.ParseAndValidateToken()`\n- Sets parsed claims in Gin context: `c.Set(\"claims\", claims)`\n- Error codes: `UNAUTHORIZED`, `TOKEN_EXPIRED`\n\n#### D. Token Flow\n```\nClient --> Router (AuthMiddleware validates client JWT)\n         --> Router signs new JWT --> PicoD (AuthMiddleware validates Router's JWT)\n```\n\n**Dependency:** `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.1` (already in go.mod)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Project Structure Overview\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n|-- go.mod                     -- Module: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube, Go 1.25.0\n|-- go.sum                     -- Dependency checksums\n|-- proposal.md                -- AR-011: Router JWT Authentication & Signing (completed proposal)\n|-- design.md                  -- AR-016: PicoD File Management API Design\n|-- delta-spec.md              -- AR-016: Delta specification for file API reorganization\n|-- project.md                 -- Project overview document\n|-- test_spec.md               -- Test specification\n|-- .sdd_prompt.md             -- SDD prompt (references AR-017)\n|\n|-- cmd/\n|   |-- picod/main.go          -- PicoD entry point\n|\n|-- pkg/\n|   |-- picod/                 -- In-sandbox daemon (command execution + file management)\n|   |   |-- files/             -- Structured file management subpackage\n|   |-- router/                -- HTTP reverse proxy with JWT auth, session management, load balancing\n|   |-- store/                 -- Redis/Valkey session store\n|   |-- apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -- Kubernetes CRD types (CodeInterpreter, AgentRuntime)\n|   |-- common/types/          -- Shared types\n|   |-- workloadmanager/       -- Sandbox lifecycle management (handler, reconciler, response)\n|\n|-- client-go/                 -- Generated Kubernetes client library\n|   |-- clientset/             -- Typed clientset\n|   |-- informers/             -- Shared informers\n|   |-- listers/               -- Listers\n|\n|-- changes/                   -- Architecture Request (AR) change folders\n|   |-- AR-001/ through AR-017/  -- Each has proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md\n|\n|-- session-routing/           -- Session routing design/spec\n|-- session-store/             -- Session store design/spec\n|-- sandbox-orchestration/     -- Sandbox orchestration design/spec\n|-- code-execution/            -- Code execution design/spec\n|-- cli-toolkit/               -- CLI toolkit design/spec\n|-- deployment/                -- Deployment design/spec, client-go docs\n|-- ci-cd/                     -- CI/CD design/spec\n|-- integrations/              -- Integrations design/spec\n|-- python-sdk/                -- Python SDK design/spec\n|-- idle-cleanup/              -- Idle cleanup design/spec\n|-- testing/                   -- TDD manifest\n|-- coverage.out               -- Test coverage output\n```\n\n**Module:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n**Go Version:** 1.25.0\n**Key Dependencies:** gin, golang-jwt/jwt/v5, k8s.io/client-go, redis/valkey, prometheus, controller-runtime\n\n---\n\n### 4. Existing Middleware Patterns\n\n#### A. PicoD Middleware (`pkg/picod/server.go`)\n```go\nengine.Use(gin.Logger(), gin.Recovery())\napi := s.engine.Group(\"/api\")\napi.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())  // JWT auth on all /api routes\n// Health endpoint is OUTSIDE the /api group -- no auth required\n```\n\n#### B. Router Middleware Stack (`pkg/router/server.go`)\n```go\nv1 := s.engine.Group(\"/v1\")\nv1.Use(gin.Logger())\nv1.Use(gin.Recovery())\nv1.Use(AuthMiddleware(s.jwtManager))         // JWT auth\nv1.Use(ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware(...))      // Rate limiting via semaphore\n// Health endpoints are registered outside /v1 group\n```\n\n#### C. Individual Middlewares (`pkg/router/middleware.go`)\n| Middleware | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `AuthMiddleware(jwtManager)` | JWT Bearer token validation, sets claims in context |\n| `ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware(max)` | Semaphore-based concurrency limiting, returns 429 when exceeded |\n| `RequestLoggerMiddleware()` | Structured request logging with duration and trace ID |\n| `TraceIDMiddleware()` | Generates UUID trace ID, sets `X-Trace-Id` header |\n\n#### D. Middleware Ordering Pattern\nThe established pattern is: `Logger -> Recovery -> AuthMiddleware -> ConcurrencyLimit -> Handler`\n\nThis ensures:\n- Unauthenticated requests don't consume concurrency quota\n- Panics are recovered before auth checks\n- All requests are logged\n\n---\n\n### 5. Existing Proposals and AR Files\n\n**Top-level proposal:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md` -- AR-011: Router JWT Authentication & Signing (fully detailed, 218 lines)\n\n**AR-017 (Current/Pending):**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/proposal.md` -- **STUB/TEMPLATE** (all TODO placeholders, 53 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/design.md` -- **STUB/TEMPLATE** (all TODO placeholders, 74 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md` -- **STUB/TEMPLATE** (single TODO task, 32 lines)\n- Title: \"AR-017 -- PicoD JWT Middleware\" -- Module: pkg/picod, Size: S\n\n**Completed ARs with full documentation (AR-001 through AR-016):**\nEach AR directory contains: `proposal.md`, `design.md`, `tasks.md`, and some have `delta-spec.md`.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Key Configuration\n\n**go.mod:**\n- Module: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n- Go: 1.25.0\n- JWT library: `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.1`\n- Web framework: `github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0`\n- K8s: `k8s.io/client-go v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/api v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/apimachinery v0.34.1`\n\n**PicoD Constants (`pkg/picod/types.go`):**\n- `TimeoutExitCode = 124`\n- `MaxBodySize = 32 << 20` (32 MiB)\n- `PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`\n\n**Router JWT Constants (`pkg/router/jwt.go`):**\n- `rsaKeySize = 2048`\n- `jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute`\n- `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe project is **AgentCube** -- a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agent code execution. The `pkg/picod` module is a well-structured in-sandbox daemon with:\n- A complete JWT authentication system already implemented (`AuthManager`)\n- Command execution with timeout and sandboxing\n- File management (both legacy handlers in `files.go` and a new structured `files/` subpackage)\n- Path sanitization preventing directory traversal\n\n**AR-017** (\"PicoD JWT Middleware\") exists as a stub/template. The JWT middleware for PicoD is already fully implemented in AR-015. AR-017 appears to be a new change request that has not yet been filled in -- its proposal.md, design.md, and tasks.md all contain only TODO placeholders.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2877b6803ffeZfumTEVuGLIKBs","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore picod and JWT context","time":{"start":1775843448825,"end":1775843581913}}}}
